name: market for wood preservation, hot/cold dipping, creosote, outdoor use, ground contact | wood preservation, hot/cold dipping, creosote, outdoor use, ground contact | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/11356/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'wood preservation, hot/cold dipping, creosote, outdoor use, ground contact', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is delivering the service of wood preservation with a hot/cold dipping method. The service represents the surface treatment of 1kg wood with creosote in a hot-cold dipping bath processs as a type of open tank impregnation, for outdoor use with ground contact. The process includes inputs of creosote, electricity and heat consumption, infrastructure, emissions and end-of-life for mineral oil used for lubrication. The input of wood is excluded and should be added manually.

This activity starts with the service generation.


This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
